A great first project is to **connect to PX4 and display the connection status**. No maps, no controls, just proving that **Qt/QML ↔ C++ ↔ MAVSDK ↔ PX4** works.

## Project structure

```text
PX4Hello/

├── CMakeLists.txt
├── main.cpp
├── Main.qml
├── backend/
│   ├── Drone.h
│   └── Drone.cpp
└── resources.qrc
```

## What it does

1. Start PX4:

```bash
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
cd ~/PX4/PX4-Autopilot
make px4_sitl gz_x500
```

2. Run your Qt app.

3. The Qt window displays:

```text
PX4 Ground Station

Status: Connected
```

If PX4 isn't running:

```text
Status: Waiting for PX4...
```

